<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,1595,1891]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Hesse, 
<number box="[390,447,1719,1742]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1956.0">1956</number>
: 
<number box="[458,485,1719,1742]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="90.0">90</number>
– described from a topotypic male in Dr Brauns collection and a female from the Little Karoo (
<collectionCode box="[549,630,1749,1772]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/94p5-pepz" name="Iziko Museums of Cape Town" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">SAMC</collectionCode>
). The topotypic male, now in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34985" box="[959,1039,1749,1772]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34985" name="KwaZulu-Natal Museum" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">NMSA</collectionCode>
, was collected in Willowmore, 
<date box="[440,550,1778,1801]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1920-12-01">
<number box="[440,449,1778,1801]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
.xii. 
<number box="[489,550,1778,1801]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1920.0">1920</number>
</date>
, and bears an old determination label, probably by Dr Brauns “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezz" authorityName="Bezz" box="[369,656,1808,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Tomomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbatula">Tomomyza barbatula Bezz</taxonomicName>
