<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1323,412,518]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,378,412,438]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
: The two males 
<typeStatus box="[580,687,412,438]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[748,906,412,438]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">paralectotype</typeStatus>
from Bezzi’s collection in 
<collectionCode box="[1233,1323,412,438]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">MSNM</collectionCode>
accord with the description given by Hesse (
<number box="[821,885,452,478]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="1956.0">1956</number>
). It is a distinctive species with an almost entirely blackish cuticle and hyaline wings.
</paragraph>
